[{"id":31209,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Synthesis of Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>&nbsp;needs nascent oxygen.","Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>&nbsp;is a synthetic and linear thermosetting polymer.","Buna-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>&nbsp;is a natural polymer.","Neoprene is an addition copolymer used in plastic bucket manufacturing."],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Buna-S is an elastomer<br /><br />Buna-N is a synthetic polymer<br /><br />Buna-S is polymerised by addition polymerisation method which needs radical initiator for chain propagation step. Nascent oxygen can be used as an Radical initiator.<br /><br />Neoprene is a synthetic rubber.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a90f48a4-6bdd-46de-98a1-3b0bfe008507-image.png\" style=\"width: 476px; height: 101px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31176,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p>Polyethene</p>","<p>Polycarbonate</p>","<p>Polyamide</p>","<p>Polyacrylonitrile</p>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The addition polymerisation of acrylonitrile in presence of a peroxide catalyst leads to the formation of polyacrylonitrile. The commercial name of polyacrylonitrile is orlon (acrilan). That is, it is used as a substitute for wool in making commercial fibres as orlon or acrilan.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ffff4193-687e-4fa5-9b67-ac8c70595f55.png\" style=\"width: 454px; height: 99px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31170,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Nylon 6 or polycaprolactam is a polymer, in particular semicrystalline polyamide.&nbsp;</p><p>Vulcanization is a chemical process in which the rubber is heated with sulphur, accelerator and activator at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>140</mn><mo>&#8211;</mo><mn>160</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>. The process involves the formation of cross-links between long rubber molecules to achieve improved elasticity, resilience, tensile strength, viscosity, hardness and weather resistance.</p><p>Polychloroprene is the polymer name for the synthetic rubber known as neoprene.</p><p>Natural rubber is the only addition polymer found in nature and is known as Cis - 1,4 - polyisoprene.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31239,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Poly vinyl chloride","Bakelite","Glyptal","Polypropene"],"answer":2,"solution":"Glyptal is polymer of glycerol and phthalic anhydride.<br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Jee_1_Quest_5_soln.jpg\" style=\"width: 346px; height: 182px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":31210,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Strength","Sulphur","Sulphonation","Styrene"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Buna--<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#39;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></math> stand for styrene.</p><p>Buna &ndash; S is a more commonly used name for a polymer named styrene butadiene rubber. The structure of Buna &ndash; S is given by:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b9e79b74-9ca9-471b-b9d0-bb2141be5df1-NCERT-Solutions-for-Class-12-Chemistry-Chapter-15-Polymers-2.png\" style=\"width: 664px; height: 143px;\" /></p><p>Buna &ndash; S is formed using the monomers butadiene and styrene.</p><p>Thus in&nbsp;Buna &ndash; S, the Bu stands for Butadiene, since butadiene is one of the constituent monomers of the given polymer. Also, Na stands for sodium and S represents the monomer Styrene used for the synthesis of the given polymer.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31254,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["teflon","nylon 6,6","polystyrene","natural rubber"],"answer":1,"solution":"nylon 6,6 is a polymer of adipic acid and hexamethylene diamine\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/wfxfVvWD7VDv7l1VPUf9RzRzjhhpvJ5lVqitwz3pef4.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2010","image":null},{"id":31235,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Both assertion and reason are correct, but the reason is not the correct explanation for the assertion.","Both assertion and reason are correct, and the reason is the correct explanation for the assertion.","Assertion in incorrect statement, but the reason is correct.","Both assertion and reason are incorrect."],"answer":1,"solution":"The strength of cellulose is improved by acetylation and then used for making packing material. Rayon (semisyntehtic polymer of cellulose)&nbsp;has superior properties than natural cotton.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31190,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A Both Assertion and Reason are true and&nbsp;Reason is the correct explanation of Assertion","Both Assertion and&nbsp;Reason are true but Reason is not the correct explanation of Assertion.","Assertion is true but&nbsp;Reason is false.","Assertion is false but Reason is true."],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><strong>Natural rubber</strong></p><p>Natural rubber is a polymer of isoprene, and obtained from natural source-latex tree. In natural rubber, isoprene units are joined together in head-to-tail fashion and all double bonds in the polymer chain have cis configurations as shown in the given figure.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2bd93ed4-0ea0-497f-b8b7-f06206945602-image.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 181px;\" /></p><p>The polymer contains cis repeating units and has a molecular weight ranging from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></math> upto&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></math></p><p>The cis arrangement of the double bonds in natural rubber prevents the rubber molecules from fitting into an ordered structure. Thus, rubber is an amorphous polymer. Because of the random coiling of its polymer chains, rubber stretches easily. When stretched, the rubber molecules are forced into a higher energy state. when the tension is released, rubber snaps back to its original random coiled state but it is nonpolar therefore statement-II is incorrect.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31179,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>(A) Glyptal polymer is used as a manufacture of paints and Lacquers</p><p>(B) Neoprene is formed by the free radical polymerisation of chloroprene. It is used for manufacturing conveyor belts, gaskets and hoses.</p><p>(C)&nbsp;Polyacrylonitrile is used as a substitute for wool in making commercial fibres as orlon or acrilan.</p><p>(D)&nbsp;Low density polythene (LDP) is chemically inert and tough but flexible and a poor conductor of electricity. Hence, it is used&nbsp;in the insulation of electricity carrying wires and manufacture of squeeze bottles, toys and flexible pipes.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31211,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iv</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mfenced><mo stretchy=\"false\">&#8594;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>(a)&nbsp;<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b76fe7c0-4678-42c8-8646-9369f3b4e0c0-image.png\" style=\"width: 94px; height: 119px;\" />Caprolactum is the monomeric&nbsp;unit of polymer Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p><p>(b) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>Chlorobuta<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></math>diene is the monomeric unit of polymer neoprene.<br />(c) Isoprene is the monomeric unit of polymer natural rubber.<br />(d) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CN</mi></math> (Acrylonitrile) is one of the monomeric unit of polymer&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Buna</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31256,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["$\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{OH}\\right)_2$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{COCH}_3$","$\\mathrm{HCHO}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/zfw3wkRdg6gRYyUAM7nIhd7h7DVc-chxl5PxBIY2riE.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2008","image":null},{"id":31175,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>III</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Thermoset plastics retain their form and stay solid under heat once cured.&nbsp;Urea-formaldehyde is an example of thermosetting polymer.&nbsp;Polymers which disintegrate by themselves over a period of time due to environmental degradation by bacteria etc. are called biodegradable polymers. Nylon-2-nylon-6 is an example of&nbsp;biodegradable polymer.&nbsp;Any artificial elastomer is referred to as synthetic rubber. Buna-N is an example of synthetic rubber.&nbsp;Polyester is a synthetic or man-made fiber material. Dacron is an example polyester.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31232,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"86\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6cea7244-5210-48d8-82a9-e4dcc95af70e-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"304\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"55\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/612676f0-8b71-49ae-887c-435530dc2063-image.png\" width=\"258\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"64\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/874d223d-341e-4744-ac82-db6619f64de8-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"288\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"65\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/04e0a3fa-3c22-416d-9f11-325a78433146-image.png\" style=\"float: left;\" width=\"189\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img height=\"73\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/950a85bc-36c7-4cda-a925-3b5e656eabbd-image.png\" width=\"382\" /></p><p><br />Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math><br />Polymer of glycine and amino caproic acid.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31185,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["isoprene and styrene","neoprene and sulphur","isoprene and sulphur","neoprene and styrene"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Natural rubber may be considered as a linear polymer of isoprene (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-methyl-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>-butadiene) and is also called as cis - <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;- polyisoprene.</p><p>To improve the physical properties, a process of vulcanisation is carried out. This process consists of heating a mixture of raw rubber with sulphur and an appropriate additive at a temperature range between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>373</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>415</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>.&nbsp;</p><p>In the manufacture of tyre rubber, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of sulphur is used as a cross linking agent. The probable structures of vulcanised rubber molecules are depicted below:</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/34130c56-8b3e-4559-aeb3-2fc8e77439c5-9756187_Sol.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 175px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31177,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Teflon","Dacron","Nylon 6, 6","Nylon 6"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Caprolactam is a cyclic amide. Caprolactam when heated at high temperature in presence of water, gives Nylon 6.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0c2f0ecd-80d4-4778-aff2-185aff623301-9895891.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 210px;\" />&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31171,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A(II), B(IV), C(I), D(III)","A(II), B(I), C(IV), D(III)","A(IV), B(I), C(III), D(II)","A(IV), B(III), C(I), D(II)"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></math>chloro<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></math>butadiene can undergo polymerization to form a polymer known as polychloroprene. Polychloroprene&nbsp;is a synthetic rubber commonly known as neoprene.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b3ed2d1f-3c27-4aa6-93b3-22b4b33bc44b.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 81px;\" /></p><p>Polyacrylonitrile (PAN) is an addition polymer. Addition polymers are formed through a polymerization process called addition polymerization, where monomers add to each other without the loss of any small molecules.&nbsp; Nylon-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-nylon-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;Biodegradable polymer.&nbsp;Dacron is a type of polyester. Polyester is a polymer that belongs to the polyester family of polymers.</p><p>So, A-II; B-I; C-IV; D-III</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31173,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["High density polythene","Polyacrylonitrile","Low density polythene","Polytetrafluoroethane"],"answer":0,"solution":"High-density polyethylene (HDPE) is commonly prepared in the presence of a Ziegler-Natta catalyst.&nbsp;<p>The information provided describes the preparation and characteristics of a high-density polyethylene (HDPE) polymer. HDPE is a widely used thermoplastic polymer known for its high strength, durability, and excellent chemical resistance.</p><p>The presence of trimethylammoniumpropyl (TMP) and titanium tetrachloride (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>TiCl</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>) indicates that the polymerization process is likely carried out using a Ziegler-Natta catalyst system. This catalyst system enables the production of high-density polyethylene by controlling the polymerization conditions.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31184,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Novolacs&nbsp;are phenol-formaldehyde resins with a formaldehyde to phenol molar ratio of less than one.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bce89a9b-2b73-4072-b431-73850e2406b7-image.png\" style=\"width: 487px; height: 280px;\" /></p><p>The rubber obtained is also&nbsp;called Styrene butadiene rubber (SBR). In Buna-S, Bu stands for butadiene and, Na for sodium and S for styrene. It is vulcanised with sulfur. The rubber is slightly inferior to natural rubber in its physical properties.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8e53b179-9e27-4ca1-a4f4-c730da7907a9-image.png\" style=\"width: 379px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>Glyptal- a polyester is formed by ethylene glycol and phthalic acid by step-growth polymerization.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d5455332-73a6-45f9-9fd8-23abe21036aa-image.png\" style=\"width: 527px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>Dacron obtained by condensation polymerisation of ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>420</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>460</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>&nbsp;using zinc acetate and antimony oxide as catalyst.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4e850628-0f8e-44f3-a570-476eab17f3ea-image.png\" style=\"width: 566px; height: 140px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31196,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>","Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>","Dacron","Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>S</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>(a) Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;is the polymer of hexamethylene diamine and adipic acid. It is made by the condensation of given monomers.</p><p>(b) Nylon<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;os also a condensation polymer of caprolactum. It is a polymide.</p><p>(c) Dacron is also a condensation polymer of ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid. It is an example of polyester.</p><p>(d) Buna<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>S</mi></math>&nbsp;is an addition polymer of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;butadiene and styrene.</p><p>Hence, only (4) is not a condensation polymer.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;(4) is the correct option.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31248,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["$4900$","$4600$","$4300$","$5200$"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":31183,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Neoprene (CR), also called polychloroprene or chloroprene rubber, synthetic rubber produced by the polymerization (or linkage together of single molecules into giant, multiple-unit molecules) of chloroprene.</p><p>Natural rubber is polyisoprene. It is a polymer of hydrocarbon-isoprene. Polyisoprene is an addition polymer. It is&nbsp;cis-1,&nbsp;4-polyisoprene.</p><p>Teflon is a brand name for a synthetic chemical called polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE). Orlon is made from polymerized acrylonitrile.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a8afac8b-940b-4b9b-b9a3-e8279e772cc7-image.png\" style=\"width: 413px; height: 100px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/40f74114-0024-49cb-bf61-445df3737438-image.png\" style=\"width: 342px; height: 70px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4ee885f7-c6cd-4ce6-afaa-c1e4f23dc7b9-image.png\" style=\"width: 368px; height: 80px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/eeb67c17-c981-43ae-9858-f0346e66355d-image.png\" style=\"width: 380px; height: 90px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31186,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width: 350px;\">\t<tbody>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Column I</td>\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Column II</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</td>\t\t\t<td>Nylon-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn></math></td>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\">III</td>\t\t\t<td>Bristles of brush</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>.</td>\t\t\t<td>Low density polythene</td>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\">IV</td>\t\t\t<td>Toys</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>.</td>\t\t\t<td>High density polythene</td>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\">I</td>\t\t\t<td>Buckets</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math>.</td>\t\t\t<td>Teflon</td>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\">II</td>\t\t\t<td>Non-stick utensils</td>\t\t</tr>\t</tbody></table><p>Teflon is&nbsp;a brand name for a synthetic chemical called polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE). Teflon is used to coat a variety of products because it&#39;s waterproof, cuts down on friction, and creates a nonstick surface.</p><p>Nylon 66 is a type of polyamide or nylon. It, and nylon 6, are the two most common for textile and plastic industries. Nylon 66 is made of two monomers each containing 6 carbon atoms, hexamethylenediamine and adipic acid, which give nylon 66 its name.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31257,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Teflon","Nylon – 66","Terylene","Bakelite"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/lJNpOZsLAUhs8BPRv3ga6rGn4VnRj_1KKhFnsCAoCLg.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":31198,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["glycerol and phthalic acid","ethylene glycol and phthalic acid","ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid","glycerol and terephthalic acid"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/efea678a-81d5-4f77-9377-c9f4493ea8a0-02a290e8-1b00-4c86-afb6-3e4a9da5dfc0-image.png\" style=\"width: 737px; height: 137px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31195,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/14e0caf6-38e6-419d-b887-d00544f47dc7-dc434a5f-ba26-4af6-9109-a8bc3a0579a2-88fe126a-65b7-4bab-b7ed-4b97efd0cf14-image.png\" style=\"width: 785px; height: 171px;\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; The molar mass of the monomer unit in the box&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>107</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math>Assume there are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math>number of monomer units,</p><p>So, total molar mass&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>107</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>963</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31172,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<strong>Statement I&nbsp;</strong>is<strong> </strong>false<strong>&nbsp;</strong>but<strong>&nbsp;Statement II&nbsp;</strong>is true","<strong>Statement I&nbsp;</strong>is<strong>&nbsp;</strong>true<strong>&nbsp;</strong>but<strong>&nbsp;Statement II&nbsp;</strong>is false","Both&nbsp;<strong>Statement I </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Statement II </strong>are true","Both&nbsp;<strong>Statement I </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;Statement II </strong>are false"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Low Density Polyethylene&nbsp;is obtained by the polymerisation of ethene under high pressure of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math> at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>350</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>570</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> in the presence of an initiator. High Density Polyethylene&nbsp;is obtained when polymerisation is done in the presence of Ziegler-Natta catalyst at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>333</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>343</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math> under <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math> pressure.&nbsp;Nylon-6 is manufactured from the monomer called caprolactam. The monomer caprolactam is heated at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>533</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>543</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>in an inert atmosphere, it polymerises to give nylon-6.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31206,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Polyacrylonitrile","Polyesters","Polyamide","Cellulose"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Orlon fibres are made up of Polyacrylonitrile.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2ab1c598-4766-47fd-b1b6-0b2c55f98002-6b4b43ba-b2be-4dd6-8681-b065c7ca13f9-image.png\" style=\"width: 159px; height: 97px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":31243,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["Dacron","Neoprene","Teflon","Acrylonitrile"],"answer":0,"solution":"Dacron is made by the removal of H<sub>2</sub>O&nbsp;from the constituents (phthalic&nbsp;acid) and ethylene diol.<br /><br /><u><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ca35a7c2-87cc-4e38-9a6a-e09de70a8bf0-25778.jpg\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 189px;\" /></strong></u>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (06 Apr)","image":null},{"id":31227,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<p><img height=\"136\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/37d10d93-285f-4701-92b5-d17b364dd877-image.png\" width=\"252\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"182\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/36d27e09-4002-40be-9c7d-168a00238858-image.png\" width=\"217\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"201\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f63bcdfb-9b73-4920-991c-df321f44cc6b-image.png\" width=\"241\" /></p>","<p><img height=\"147\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a67938a5-31f5-4093-9bd6-7ccd609e090b-image.png\" width=\"273\" /></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img height=\"369\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/25ca80b3-a520-4845-85f2-c83f642a303a-image.png\" width=\"586\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":31169,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Polymers","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>III</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>IV</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>IV</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>III</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>III</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>IV</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>II</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>III</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi>IV</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Orlon is a man-made polymer of acrylonitrile. Thus, its monomer is vinyl cyanide or Prop-2-ene-1-nitrile.&nbsp;Natural Rubber is obtained from latex which is a sap of a tree. Natural rubber is a polymer of isoprene.&nbsp;Teflon is made of a chemical compound named polytetrafluoroethylene (PTFE) which is a synthetic fluoropolymer.&nbsp;Nylon-6 is produced by ring-opening chain growth polymerisation of caprolactam in the presence of water vapour and an acid catalyst at the melt.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (15 Apr Shift 1)","image":null}]